The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Raman to sign deal
                                                                                                                       7                                      Raman to sign deal
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The hunt for Bengal coach is finally over. Former India opener W.V. Raman is set to sign a two-year contract with the Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB).         
	It will be Ramans second stint as Bengal coach after the 2001-02 season, when Bengal reached the semi-finals of the Ranji Trophy. He has been the Tamil Nadu coach during the past few seasons.         
	The only impediment in Ramans appointment was his obtaining the release order from the Tamil Nadu Cricket Association (TNCA). However, that issue has now been sorted out and the CAB is set unveil him in a couple of days.         
	Raman, who will be replacing Roger Binny, pipped Paras Mhambrey and Ashok Malhotra  the others who were in the fray  to bag the job.                                                                                                                     
